@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #F8FAFC
skinparam handwritten false
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment left
skinparam wrapWidth 240
skinparam maxMessageSize 200

skinparam participant {
  BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  BorderColor     #4A5568
  FontSize        12
  FontColor       #1A202C
  FontStyle       bold
  Padding         12
}
skinparam actor {
  BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  BorderColor     #2B6CB0
  FontSize        12
  FontColor       #1A202C
  FontStyle       bold
}
skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor #FFFFF0
  BorderColor     #B7791F
  FontSize        11
  FontColor       #1A202C
  FontStyle       bold
}
skinparam queue {
  BackgroundColor #FFF5F5
  BorderColor     #C53030
  FontSize        11
  FontColor       #1A202C
  FontStyle       bold
}
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor                #2C5282
  ArrowFontSize             11
  ArrowFontColor            #2D3748
  ArrowThickness            1
  LifeLineBorderColor       #CBD5E0
  LifeLineBorderThickness   1
  LifeLineBackgroundColor   #EDF2F7
  BoxBorderColor            #A0AEC0
  BoxFontSize               12
  BoxFontStyle              bold
  BoxFontColor              #1A202C
  BoxBackgroundColor        transparent
  DividerBackgroundColor    #EBF4FF
  DividerBorderColor        #3182CE
  DividerBorderThickness    1
  DividerFontSize           11
  DividerFontColor          #1A365D
  DividerFontStyle          bold
  ActivationBorderColor     #2B6CB0
  ActivationBackgroundColor #BEE3F8
  ParticipantPadding        20
  BoxPadding                18
  MessageAlign              left
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FFFBEB
  BorderColor     #D69E2E
  FontSize        10
  FontColor       #744210
}

title
  <size:17><b>OEX Optimisation Platform</b></size>
  <size:11><color:#718096>End-to-End Sequence · Steps 1–18</color></size>
end title

'─────────────────────────────────────────────────
' Participants
'─────────────────────────────────────────────────

actor       "User"          as USER

box "<b>OEX Channel</b>" #EBF8FF
  participant "OEX UI"      as UI
  participant "OGW"         as OGW
  participant "OSB MS\n<size:10>(OEX APIs)</size>" as OSB
end box

box "<b>Network Edge</b>" #F0FFF4
  participant "NGW"         as NGW
end box

box "<b>Optimisation Platform</b>" #FFFFF0
  participant "OC MS"       as OC
  participant "OD MS"       as OD
  database    "OC MS DB"    as OCDB
  database    "OC MS\nOutbox" as Outbox
  database    "OC MS\nInbox"  as Inbox
end box

box "<b>Event Fabric</b>" #FFF5F5
  queue "Kafka\n<size:10>t7.optimisation.events</size>" as Kafka
end box

box "<b>Solver Execution</b>" #FAF5FF
  participant "Python /\nGurobi Worker" as Worker
  participant "Gurobi\nOptimiser"       as Gurobi
end box

'═════════════════════════════════════════════════
== 1–2 · User initiates optimisation journey ==
'═════════════════════════════════════════════════

USER -> UI  : [1] Open OEX UI\nInitiate optimisation journey
UI   -> OGW : [2] Submit optimisation request

'═════════════════════════════════════════════════
== 3–6 · Channel routing through to OC MS ==
'═════════════════════════════════════════════════

OGW  -> OSB : [3] Invoke OSB MS\n<color:#2B6CB0><i>mTLS + User Context JWT</i></color>
activate OSB
OSB  -> OSB : [4] Validate User Context JWT\nShape OEX request / action model
OSB  -> NGW : [5] POST /optimisation\n<color:#2B6CB0><i>mTLS + OAuth2 system-to-system</i></color>
deactivate OSB
NGW  -> OC  : [6] Route request to OC MS
activate OC

'═════════════════════════════════════════════════
== 7–8 · OC MS validates against OD MS contract ==
'═════════════════════════════════════════════════

OC   -> OD  : [7] Validate ACTIVE OptimisationSpecification\nand retrieve request contract\n<color:#2B6CB0><i>mTLS</i></color>
activate OD
OD  --> OC  : ACTIVE OptimisationSpecification + request contract
deactivate OD

OC   -> OC  : [8] Validate constraints[] · targets[] · context[]\n<i>against OD MS request contract</i>

'═════════════════════════════════════════════════
== 9–10 · OC MS persists and emits (single transaction) ==
'═════════════════════════════════════════════════

group <color:#276749><b>Atomic DB Transaction</b></color>
  OC -> OCDB   : [9] Persist runtime Optimisation\n<i>lifecycleStatus = ACKNOWLEDGED</i>
  activate OCDB
  OCDB --> OC  : OK
  deactivate OCDB

  OC -> Outbox : [10] Write OptimisationRequestedEvent\n<i>instruction = EXECUTE</i>
  activate Outbox
  Outbox --> OC : OK
  deactivate Outbox
end

OC --> NGW : 202 Accepted\n<i>Location: /optimisation/{id} · ETag: opt-rev1</i>
deactivate OC

NGW  --> OSB : 202 Accepted
OSB  --> OGW : 202 Accepted
OGW  --> UI  : 202 Accepted
UI   --> USER: Request accepted\n<i>jobId returned to UI</i>

'═════════════════════════════════════════════════
== 11 · Outbox relay publishes to Kafka ==
'═════════════════════════════════════════════════

note over Outbox, Kafka
  <b>[11] Transactional Outbox Pattern</b>
  Relay polls committed outbox rows and
  publishes to Kafka — at-least-once delivery
end note

Outbox ->> Kafka : OptimisationRequestedEvent\n<i>instruction=EXECUTE · correlationId · inputs · spec ref</i>

'═════════════════════════════════════════════════
== 12–15 · Worker consumes, resolves, solves, publishes ==
'═════════════════════════════════════════════════

Kafka -> Worker : [12] Consume OptimisationRequestedEvent\n<i>(idempotency check on correlationId)</i>
activate Worker

Worker -> Worker : [13] Resolve internal deterministic\n       model binding from spec ref

Worker -> Gurobi : [14] Invoke Gurobi Optimiser
activate Gurobi
Gurobi --> Worker : Solve result\n<i>SUCCESS · INFEASIBLE · FAILURE</i>
deactivate Gurobi

Worker ->> Kafka : [15] Publish outcome event\n<i>OptimisationCompletedEvent  or  OptimisationFailedEvent\ncorrelationId · outcome · outputs</i>
deactivate Worker

'═════════════════════════════════════════════════
== 16–17 · OC MS Inbox projects outcome ==
'═════════════════════════════════════════════════

Kafka -> Inbox : [16] Consume worker outcome event
activate Inbox
note right of Inbox
  Idempotency check —
  guard against duplicate delivery
end note

Inbox -> OCDB  : [17] Update OC MS DB\n<i>lifecycleStatus = COMPLETED / INFEASIBLE / FAILED\nresult.outcome · result.outputs</i>
activate OCDB
OCDB --> Inbox : OK
deactivate OCDB
deactivate Inbox

'═════════════════════════════════════════════════
== 18 · User polls for current status / result ==
'═════════════════════════════════════════════════

loop [18] Poll until lifecycleStatus is terminal
  USER -> UI  : Poll — check optimisation status
  UI   -> OGW : GET /optimisation/{id}
  OGW  -> OSB : Forward\n<color:#2B6CB0><i>mTLS + User Context JWT</i></color>
  activate OSB
  OSB  -> NGW : Forward\n<color:#2B6CB0><i>mTLS + OAuth2 system-to-system</i></color>
  deactivate OSB
  NGW  -> OC  : GET /optimisation/{id}
  activate OC
  OC   -> OCDB : Load Optimisation state
  activate OCDB
  OCDB --> OC  : Optimisation row
  deactivate OCDB
  OC  --> NGW  : 200 Optimisation\n<i>lifecycleStatus · result when terminal</i>
  deactivate OC
  NGW  --> OSB : Response
  OSB  --> OGW : Response
  OGW  --> UI  : Response
  UI  --> USER : Render current status / result
end

@enduml
